sections.Learning outcomes:
After completion of the course the student should be able to:
1. Knowledge and understanding
• describe why energy aware computing is an important current topic;
• describe the electrical mechanisms that cause power and energy to be dissipated;
• describe various circuit techniques for reducing power dissipation and, in particular, evaluate the effect of reducing frequency and supply voltage on performance, power and energy;
• describe various computer architecture, memory, and secondary storage techniques for reducing energy usage.
2. Skills and abilities
• demonstrate the ability to use simulation tools to estimate the energy usage of a computer application.
3. Judgement and approach
• identify the strengths and weaknesses of different classes of computer processors, with respect to energy efficiency.
